com.esri.mo2.map.ext
Interface StoredQuery

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseStoredQuery
public interface StoredQuery
extends Cloneable

Defines a parameterized QueryFilter. A StoredQuery can be identified uniquely by name, within the context of a LayerExtension. Parameterization of the QueryFilter refers to the process of identifying one or more values within the QueryFilter's WHERE clause, and allowing run-time replacement of those values.

Each parameter value can be identified within the WHERE clause by the special string "<%name%>" where "name" identifies the parameter and must have one or more alphanumeric characters.

For example, the following Where clause has a single String parameter value named "V1": (ADDRESS like '<%V1%>') and (ZIP = 92373). Note that the single-quote marks are required within the WHERE clause, since the field has string values. Similarly, the following example shows a Where clause with a single integer parameter value named "VZ": (ADDRESS like '%State%') and (ZIP = <%VZ%>).

createFilter

public QueryFilter createFilter(String[] values)
Creates a new, non-parameterized, QueryFilter using the specified values. The WHERE clause of the resulting QueryFilter will be created by replacing the parameters with the given values. If you want to specify a non-String replacement value, then you must convert it to String first. You don't need to supply all the parameter values - if you supply too many, the unnecessary values will be ignored, or if you supply too few, the needed values will be set to blank.

Parameters:
values - the replacement values
Returns:
the new QueryFilter containing the replacement value
Throws:
IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the parameterized WhereClause is invalid with respect to the defined parameters.
